</i></p><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-17_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Healthcare professionals, particularly nurses and midwives, are essential to delivering safe, effective, and compassionate care. The Nursing and Midwifery Council (NMC) is the regulatory body that maintains standards and ensures the competence and conduct of nursing and midwifery professionals in the UK. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune delves into understanding the NMC's role, which is crucial for organisations aiming to meet statutory and regulatory compliance. </span>
</p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-9838" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-knuQPt cVHHwo pf-19_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-kRRxPL eBhmAi"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-20_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-iapVNj iUcVvL pf-21_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-22_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kMriOJ brNffh pf-24_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-25_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regulation scope</strong> - The NMC regulates approximately 700,000 nurses, midwives, and nursing associates.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-27_ pf-text-1"><strong>Fitness to practise</strong> - In 2022, the NMC received around 5,000 fitness to practise referrals, highlighting its role in maintaining professional standards.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-29_ pf-text-1"><strong>Educational standards </strong>- The NMC approves over 1,000 nursing and midwifery education programmes across the UK, ensuring consistent training quality.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-31_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-iapVNj iUcVvL pf-32_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-33_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kMriOJ brNffh pf-35_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-36_ pf-text-1"><strong>NMC (Nursing and Midwifery Council) </strong>- An independent regulatory body for nursing and midwifery professionals in the UK, established to protect the public.&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-38_ pf-text-1"><strong>Fitness to practise</strong> - The process by which the NMC investigates concerns about a nurse's or midwife's ability to practise safely and effectively.


</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-40_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-iapVNj iUcVvL pf-41_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-42_ pf-heading-1-h3">The NMC's role and responsibilities</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-44_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Setting standards</strong></h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-46_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The NMC sets education, training, conduct, and performance standards. These standards ensure that nurses and midwives provide high-quality care throughout their careers. The NMC's Code of Conduct outlines the professional behaviour expected from registrants, focusing on prioritising people, practising effectively, preserving safety, and promoting professionalism and trust.
</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-48_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Education and training</strong></h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-50_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The NMC approves and monitors educational institutions and programmes. By setting standards for education, the NMC ensures that nurses and midwives have the necessary skills and knowledge from the start of their careers. Regular reviews and updates to the curriculum ensure that training remains relevant and of high quality.

</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-52_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Registration</strong></h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-54_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Nurses and midwives must be registered with the NMC to practise in the UK. The registration process includes verifying qualifications, ensuring fitness to practise, and maintaining ongoing professional development. This safeguards the public by ensuring that only qualified individuals can provide care.


</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-56_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Fitness to practise</strong></h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-58_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The NMC investigates complaints and concerns about registrants' fitness to practise. This includes issues related to professional misconduct, lack of competence, and health concerns. The fitness to practise process is designed to protect patients and the public by addressing serious concerns and taking appropriate action, ranging from warnings to removal from the register.

</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-60_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-iapVNj iUcVvL pf-61_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-62_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommended best practices for compliance</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-64_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Understanding and implementing the NMC code</strong></h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-66_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Healthcare organisations should ensure that all nursing and midwifery staff understand and adhere to the NMC Code. Regular training and workshops can help reinforce the code's importance and application in daily practice.

</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-68_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Continuous Professional Development (CPD)</strong></h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-70_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Nurses and midwives must engage in CPD to maintain their registration. Organisations can support this by providing access to relevant training and development opportunities, ensuring staff can meet the NMC's CPD requirements.


</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-72_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Robust reporting mechanisms</strong></h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-74_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Establishing precise and confidential reporting mechanisms for professional conduct concerns can help organisations promptly address issues. This aligns with the NMC's focus on maintaining public trust and safety.



</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-76_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Utilising compliance management software</strong></h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-78_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Implementing tools like ComplyPlus™ can streamline regulatory compliance management. Such software helps track training, monitor adherence to standards, and ensure timely updates on legislative changes.


</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-80_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-iapVNj iUcVvL pf-81_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-82_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations</h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-84_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To effectively comply with NMC regulations and promote high standards of care, healthcare organisations should:



</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kMriOJ brNffh pf-86_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-87_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regularly review and update policies</strong> - Ensure all policies align with the latest NMC standards and guidelines.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-89_ pf-text-1"><strong>Provide ongoing training </strong>- Facilitate continuous education and professional development for nursing and midwifery staff.&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-91_ pf-text-1"><strong>Implement effective reporting systems</strong> - Encourage the reporting of concerns and ensure a supportive environment for whistleblowers.&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bdOgOc bNKfVA pf-93_ pf-text-1"><strong>Leverage technology </strong>- Use compliance management software like ComplyPlus™ to maintain and track adherence to regulations efficiently.


</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-95_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-iapVNj iUcVvL pf-96_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-97_ pf-heading-1-h3">Conclusion
</h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-99_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>The Nursing and Midwifery Council (NMC) is critical in safeguarding public health by regulating nursing and midwifery standards. By understanding the NMC's responsibilities and implementing best practices, healthcare organisations can ensure compliance, enhance care quality, and protect patient safety.











